p.span: The Hamilton Township School District’s Food Services Department will make every attempt to provide meals for all students enrolled in our district during this crisis.

span.style: line-height: 107%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;

p.span: William Davies Middle School is a pick up process through the main entrance drive through. When you arrive, leave your windows up and remain in your car until instructed to pull up. And most importantly, please remember social distancing.

span.style: line-height: 107%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;

p.span: Shaner Pick up is at the parent pick up Main front entrance between the hours of 9:30-11

span.style: line-height: 107%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;

p.span: Distribution dates are listed below for all students Pre-K-8 on a first come first served basis.

span.style: line-height: 107%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;

p.span: (Lunches will include milk, fruit, and a peanut butter and jelly sandwich)

span.style: line-height: 107%; font-size: 14pt; font-family: "Comic Sans MS";

div.p: The Peanut butter and jelly sandwich may be frozen and can be kept frozen for up to one month. Simply refrigerate the sandwich to defrost. If you plan on eating the sandwich within an hour, you may defrost on the counter at room temperature. Fresh fruit such as apples and oranges should be refrigerated. Breakfast items such as dried craisins and raisins do not require refrigeration.
